node.title: Why You Sexually Repel Your Partner ⚡️❌

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Healer | Podcast Host on July 29, 2021. May be an image of text that says '"How can I tell if he's into me?" @_JAKEWOODARD The conscious masculine will show that he likes you with his integrity, consistency, and action. He will be focused on his mission, but he will make time to SEE you. The unconscious masculine will play mind games and hope you chase him around like a little boy. You will get very frustrated with this type of man because you won't know where you stand in his life because he still doesn't know where he stands in his own life.'.

node.text:
“𝙄 𝙖𝙢 𝙣𝙤𝙩 𝙨𝙪𝙧𝙚 𝙞𝙛 𝙝𝙚 𝙞𝙨 𝙞𝙣𝙩𝙤 𝙢𝙚” 🤷‍♀️

If a masculine man is ”into you,” then you will know it based on the level of interest he shows you.

If he’s playing games, you will know it.

When a masculine man is truly interested in a woman, he will naturally want to make her feel seen.

He will want to pursue her.
He will want to take her out.
He will be consistent with her.

Yes. There are flighty, Peter Pan men that exist, and you won’t know where you stand with them because they are still unsure of themselves.

So how can you call in a conscious masculine man?

🔥 I am going to be teaching this in my upcoming course, “The Magnetic Feminine.” Which guides women through a step-by-step process of how to heal their inner masculine, activate their divine feminine essence, and attract the man they desire.

You can signup for the waitlist and get 50% off when the course goes live on August 17th. The link is in my bio!

Sending you love + blessings,
-Jake

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Healer | Podcast Host on July 28, 2021. May be an image of ocean and text that says 'The feminine like islike the ocean. She has a magnetic pull, waves of ever-changing emotions, and powerful radiance. The integrated masculine doesn't try to change or fix the feminine. With their deep presence they can hold her flow. -Jake Woodard'.

node.text:
🔥 A wise man will not try to control her flow. Instead, he will dance with it.

When he senses her feeling emotional or sensitive, he doesn’t analyze her like a weatherman.

He’s grounded.
He’s present.
He’s consistent.
He’s clear with his direction.

His breath is slow and steady.
His energy penetrates her aura.

Allowing her to feel supported.
To feel held.
To feel safe.
To feel protected.

This does not mean he tolerates any form of abuse from her.

With his strength and her receptivity, the flower of her heart starts to open back up to the fullness of her feminine radiance.

This feminine radiance illuminates our earth.

It’s the waves of the ocean.
The vibrancy of nature.
The dancing life-force energy that moves through all of us

She is the ultimate creator and destroyer.

She is the divine mother.

Without her essence that lives within all of us, our world would be gray and dull, filled with robots. 🤖

Drop a “❤️” and TAG 3 people who need to see this.

Sending you love + blessings,
-Jake

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Healer | Podcast Host on July 25, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Intimacy requires depth. Vulnerability. Rawness. Facing your fears. Being uncomfortable. Don't let this filtered and photoshopped world make you think otherwise. -Jake Woodard'.

node.text:
🔥 Our overly guarded way of being has put limits on our ability to go deep with another person. To access the rich and healing powers of intimacy, you must be willing to go beyond your ego and step into your shadows.

Drop a “❤️” and TAG 3 people who need to see this!

Sending you love + blessings,
-Jake

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Healer | Podcast Host on July 22, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'When most people have sex, their mind is usually distracted. Fantasizing about other people, wondering how they look, or what they will eat for their next meal. They aren't present with the other person. This type of connection will almost always burn out because it lacks depth. True intimacy requires presence and vulnerability. -Jake Woodard'.

node.text:
🔥 Distracted Intimacy

Something better.
Something newer.
Something more.

We’ve created a culture of more is better and sooner is best.

Don’t like your partner? Don’t worry, you can just swipe right and get a new one.

Don’t you see how problematic this disposable way of being is?

My relationship with melissa has been 3 years of uphill growth.

Hell, we even broke up twice.

But guess what?

It’s been the best damn 3 years of my life.

That’s why I got my hillbilly ass down on one knee and asked her to marry me.

And don’t get it twisted. I was scared to ask her that.

I cried and stuttered the entire time as I gave my proposal speech.

But I was empowered.
Liberated from my ego.

Intimacy requires depth.
Vulnerability.
Rawness.
Facing your fears.
Being uncomfortable.

Don’t let this filtered and photoshopped world make you think otherwise.

Tell me, what's been your experience with intimacy?

Sending you love + blessings,
-Jake

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Healer | Podcast Host on July 21, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Ask me a question! am only answering a select few! How do you keep your man interested? @_JAKEWOODARD If you do things to "keep him interested," you'll end up constantly trying to prove your worth to him. My advice is to embody the badass goddess that you are, and if he isn't interested in that, he can drag his ass.'.

node.text:
🔥 This goes for ALL relationships. If you worry about keeping someone interested, you’re not aligned with your true authentic self.

People-pleasing isn’t attractive.

Authenticity is.

Who needed to hear this?

If you haven’t listened to episode 229: When To Let Go Of A Relationship, I highly recommend it. Go to the link in my bio, and you can tune in on podcast or YouTube!

Drop me a “❤️” and TAG 3 people who need to see this!

Sending you love + healing,
-Jake

node.text:
👇 The Feminine Doesn’t Want To Be Fixed (PLEASE READ)

Let me tell you a story about Rick + Ashley.

Rick is a masculine man, and Ashley is a feminine woman.

Ashley had a long day at work. Her boss gave her an overwhelming amount of tasks to complete.

When she gets home, she feels so stressed out. She could break down and cry at any moment.

When Rick sees her that night, he asks her, “what’s wrong?” He can sense that she’s feeling very stressed.

She starts explaining to Rick about the horrible day she had and how she feels overwhelmed at her job.

Rick immediately goes into problem-solving mode. In his masculine mind at this moment, she’s become a project for him to fix.

He tells her what she needs to be doing differently. He starts giving her the “solution” for her problems.

Although his intentions to help Ashley are pure, he’s adding to her stress at this moment because she feels like something is wrong with her.

What could he have done differently?

Listened to her.
Gazed into her eyes.
Hugged her.
Danced with her.
Supported her.

Of course, she must be open to him at this moment because he cannot support her if she’s unwilling to be supported.

Remember. Her emotions are not a puzzle to solve.

What’s been your experience with this?

Sending you love + blessings,
-Jake

node.text:
👇 How Can The Masculine Penetrate The Feminine Heart?

First, please understand that this can apply to all relationships because we all have both masculine + feminine forces within us.

In the example of a masculine man and a feminine woman, I will break down how deep intimacy occurs.

For a man to penetrate a woman’s deep heart, she must first be open + receptive to masculine energy. If she’s guarded because of past wounds, she won’t be able to fully receive him because of the closure of her heart.

Once she is open, he must learn the art of presence, integrity, and consistency.

It’s these three things that are pillars for accessing her deep heart.

Many men are very scattered and in their ego. 

They are chasing the next high or thrill.
Distracted by every shiny object.

She will never open to this type of flighty man and gain access to her cosmic garden.

And let me tell you from personal experience.

When you gain access to a woman’s cosmic garden, it’s an eternal flow of radiance and nourishment.

The paradox is, many men seek feminine energy in so many forms, and they don’t even realize they are doing it.

If you cultivate love with a good woman, your mission becomes so much more clear and balanced with her feminine energy by your side.

It’s not about how many chicks you can hook up with and how big you can inflate your ego.

I am far more impressed by a man who can focus his energy on his sacred mission and cultivate love with a single woman.

She is like a well. Get through the bedrock, and you will have an endless source of water to to hydrate your soul.

What’s been your experience with all of this?

Sending you love + blessings,
-Jake

node.text:
👇The Misconception Of Masculinity

Our world has taught us that masculinity is:

Tough
Macho
Never shows emotions
Dominant
Aggressive
Controlling

This is all false masculinity.

This “macho jerk” energy that people project is deeply rooted in insecurities and pain they mask.

How do I know?

Because I lived in that space for a very long time.

When I started to awaken from the illusion, I saw how toxic my patterns were, and the how corrupt the conditioning I received was.

The awakened masculine is here to help support the expansion of consciousness.

Don’t allow false programming to bend your perception of what true masculinity is.

When you encounter conscious masculinity, you will know by their impeccable words, integrity, + actions.

They aren’t a spiritual playboy.

They are rock solid to their core.
 
What’s been your experience with awakened masculine vs. wounded masculine?

Sending you love + blessings,
-Jake

node.text:
👇 Our relationship almost didn’t make it

For the longest time, I feared a deeper commitment.

Even for part of my relationship with Melissa, I still struggled to be “all in.”

I figured that by being in a committed relationship, I would miss out on something else. That meant I would be giving up my freedom.

I was scared as hell of deeper intimacy.

All these thoughts and old stories were running through my mind...

What if she saw me vulnerable?
What if we failed?
What if I couldn’t fully commit?

All of these “what if’s” blocked me for a long time.

I sat with my discomfort for so long.

We even broke up twice...

Then one day, it finally clicked inside of me.

Looking into her eyes, I saw her radiance. I felt this overwhelming sense of love from her.

I thought to myself, “what the hell are you doing?”

What more could you possibly want in a relationship?

She loves me unconditionally.
She’s funny and playful.
She’s intelligent and hard-working.
She’s beautiful inside and out.
She lights up the world around her with her radiance.

And I knew then it was time to move into a deeper commitment.

You see, a relationship is like a well.

You can go through life and dig a bunch of shallow wells, or you can dig a deep well.

It’s only in the deep well that you get to the richest, most pure water.

A shallow well will only give you muddy water.

The truth is, you know if someone is aligned with you or when it’s time to move on.

Don’t be afraid to open your heart and love fully...even if you’re nervous.

What’s been your experience with finding true love with a partner?

Sending you love + blessings,
-Jake
